        | This program can be generally categorized into two tracks, including 
        b “Advanced Structure & Smart Control” 
        | and
        b “Sustainable Chemical and Materials Science Smart Technology”. 
        | The track of “Advanced Structure & Smart Control” is majorly supported by faculty members from the departments of 
        b Mechanical Engineering 
        | and 
        b Civil and Construction Engineering
        | , and the track of “Sustainable Chemical and Materials Science Smart Technology” is majorly supported by faculty members from the departments of 
        b Chemical Engineering 
        | and 
        b Materials Science 
        | and Engineering. All the admitted students in this program are required to take 128 credits at least for Bachelor of Science degree (B.S).